<item>
            <title>[LU-5172] lustre-initialization-1: kernel BUG at lib/string.c:227</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5172</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;andreas.dilger@intel.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c8a7371a-efbe-11e3-a974-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c8a7371a-efbe-11e3-a974-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test lustre-initialization_1 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;kernel BUG at lib/string.c:227!&lt;br/&gt;
invalid opcode: 0000 &lt;a href=&quot;#1&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt; SMP &lt;br/&gt;
Pid: 2624, comm: mount.lustre Not tainted 2.6.32-431.17.1.el6_lustre.g357ff2e.x86_64 #1 Red Hat KVM&lt;br/&gt;
RIP: 0010:&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffff8128a30b&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;ffffffff8128a30b&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; strlcat+0x7b/0x80&lt;br/&gt;
Process mount.lustre (pid: 2624, threadinfo ffff88007a9ac000, task ffff88005f4ae080)&lt;br/&gt;
Call Trace:&lt;br/&gt;
 lmd_parse+0x12b2/0x1de0 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;obdclass&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 ? obd_zombie_is_idle+0x1e/0x70 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;obdclass&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 lustre_fill_super+0x76/0x530 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;obdclass&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 get_sb_nodev+0x5f/0xa0&lt;br/&gt;
 lustre_get_sb+0x25/0x30 &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;obdclass&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 vfs_kern_mount+0x7b/0x1b0&lt;br/&gt;
 do_kern_mount+0x52/0x130&lt;br/&gt;
 do_mount+0x2fb/0x930&lt;br/&gt;
 sys_mount+0x90/0xe0&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Info required for matching: lustre-initialization-1 lustre-initialization_1&lt;/p&gt;</description>
